Just a reminder SMI Vantage will be delisted on 2nd Sept 2024.Which means after 2nd Sept   SMI shareholders will not be able to sell off your shares already and will be holding shares in a delisted stock.It’s a hard decision to make as the losses sustained from such a drop would have been quite significant. This happened too fast and sudden and caught many off guard.From my understanding  once delisted  the only way for SMI shareholder to get back money would be- SMI management offering to buy back shares at an agreed price per share so they may privatise- SMI perhaps getting an external investment/acquisition or miracle turnaround in a big way  bringing its market value to over $40m and then re-apply for a listing status etc.If they don’t do any of the above  they remain a delisted counter (not sure how long a counter may be termed as delisted too)Anyways IF during the delisted period  SMI decides to issue div  shareholders would be entitled too.(Unlikely though)Tough decision
